.TH "generic_splice_sendpage" 9 "generic_splice_sendpage" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
generic_splice_sendpage \- splice data from a pipe to a socket
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" generic_splice_sendpage
.BI "(struct pipe_inode_info *pipe "  ","
.BI "struct file *out "  ","
.BI "loff_t *ppos "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "unsigned int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pipe" 12
pipe to splice from
.IP "out" 12
socket to write to
.IP "ppos" 12
position in \fIout\fP
.IP "len" 12
number of bytes to splice
.IP "flags" 12
splice modifier flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Will send \fIlen\fP bytes from the pipe to a network socket. No data copying
is involved.
